Title: Object: The king Psammetichus of Egypt in love with Rhodope.
Description: King seated in a room, head in profile to left, holding Rhodope's left hand with his right; Rhodope to left, head in profile to right, down on her left knee; in an oval; after A Kauffman; open-letter state. 1782 Etching with stipple
Curator's comments: Pair to 'The beautiful Rhodope in love with Aesop' (not in BM).
Bibliographic references: Calabi & De Vesme 1928 / Francesco Bartolozzi. Catalogue des estampes et notice biographique d'après les manuscrits de A. De Vesme entièrement réformés et complétés d'une étude critique par A. Calabi (1354.II)
Alexander 1992 / Chronological checklist of singly issued English prints after Angelica Kauffman (144)
